          <h1>About Us</h1>
           <p>A seasoned Banker and a political administrator. Adamu Alhaji Lawan has a long career in the Banking industry and now serves as Borno State's Commissioner of Finance, Budget and Economic Planning. With the ardent desire to serve society, Adamu Alhaji Lawan has delved into politics. You can interact with him on this website and follow his modest contribution to good governance in Borno. Adamu Alhaji Lawan was born in Jere Local Government Area of Borno State on 3rd June 1970. He attended Maimusari Primary School between 1976 and 1982, Government Secondary School New Marte from 1982 to 1988 where he wrote his SSCE and proceeded to University of Maiduguri in 1988. He Graduated with First Class in Agricultural Economics in 1995.</p>
           <p>Adamu Alhaji Lawan started his career as a lecturer and Departmental Examinations Officer at Kashim Ibrahim College of Education Maiduguri between December 1996 and October 1999. He then Proceeded to All States Trust Bank to start his banking career as Credit and Marketing Officer from October 1999 to August 2001.</p>
           <p>He transferred to the prestigious Zenith Bank in the Same month, taking the same position (Credit and Marketing Officer) which he held till he was a Branch Manager of Damaturu branch of the bank in April 2005, a position he held until June 2009 when he was promoted to the rank of Head Public Sector Group for Borno and Yobe States. He was promoted to Branch Head of the Maiduguri Branch of Zenith Bank in October 2010 and he held that position until he was appointed by the Kashim Shettima Government to serve as Honourable Commissioner of Works and Transport, Commissioner for Local Government and Emirate Affairs, Commissioner of Finance, Budget and Economic Planning and he still serves as such.</p> 
